H1> Menus

P> Menus are the boxes (or columns) of your site. They hold navigation, banners, login forms, custom HTML – anything you have a menu for.

SHOT> menus/menus-admin.png | Layout view with active and inactive menu pools

Q> What are menus?
A> They are items that appear in the menu areas (or columns) of your site. A menu can contain text, links, dynamic content, or any combination.

H1> Activating a menu

Q> How do I activate a menu item?
A> Open [b]Admin → Menus[/b] – you'll see the layout of the active theme with each menu area drawn out. Available (inactive) menus sit in the centre. Drag or click [b]Activate this menu[/b] to move one into a column.

STEP> Open [b]Admin → Menus[/b].
STEP> Click [b]Activate this menu[/b] on the menu you want to use.
STEP> Drag it to the area and position you prefer.
STEP> Click [b]Configure[/b] (if available) to adjust per-menu options.

H1> Custom content

Q> I need to put some text inside a menu item – how?
A> Open [b]Admin → Custom Menus[/b]. From there you can add a free-form menu containing any text or HTML; it then behaves like every other menu (activate it, place it, configure visibility).

Q> How can I change the options for a menu item?
A> If the menu exposes a configuration panel, a [b]Configure[/b] link appears on the activated box. Not every menu has one – simple navigation menus typically do not.

TIP> Visibility rules apply per menu: a single menu can be visible only to logged-in users, or only to a specific user class (see the Classes help page).
